metadata.name: Great Indian Bustard by Ratnakar Hiremath
metadata.description:
The Great Indian Bustard is an endangered species of bird with only an estimated 150 individuals remaining. 

Most of these (an estimated 122) are in the Indian state of Rajastan with the remainder dispersed through western India. 

This female photographed by Ratnakar Hiremath is believed to have been alone as the sole surviving GIB in Maharashtra state for the past 4 years. 

Ratnakar is a very talented wildlife and nature photgrapher from India. He is 20 years of age.
